name: 0.1.2 | Rage meter visual & basic spawn controls
body:
I decided I'd try and color the rage meter just because, but then I remembered that in issue #2 it asked for the ability to toggle the spawning of specific object types. Overall some slight modifications have been made and more debug options added, including the new CanDie checkbox, very useful for testing speeds without losing your work.

I'll be working on more spawning controls, like increment and other attributes, but for now I'll release this so you can provide as much feedback as possible, as soon as possible!

name: 0.1.1 | Rage meter & more debug
body:
The rage meter has been implemented! It's functions are complete and really just awaiting a nicer shell along with balancing from our lovely game designers Christian and Derek. You can access the debug menu by pressing ESCAPE and then simply click on debug menu, from there you can access sliders that control most of the values used to handle gameplay. Once you two decide on good values for the rage meter, you can simply create an issue with the numbers and I can make those the defaults!

(Shows what we currently have so designers can point out what else they would want!)
![image](https://github.com/CoolCoderMan281/Stumpy-Road/assets/112356747/bd4345a5-b284-4254-996f-0996ed743b8d)

name: 0.1.0 | Debug tools
body:
Added a pause menu (doesn't actually pause yet, it's just to get to the debug menu)
There are some sliders and toggles at the moment for values I have been told people would like to edit
while the game is running. If there are any more values you would like just open an issue.
